net.akami.mask.tree

Class CalculationTree<T extends Branch>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.akami.mask.tree.BinaryTree<T>
      • net.akami.mask.tree.CalculationTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - What kind of branch is handled by the tree
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DerivativeTree, ReducerTree

    public abstract class CalculationTree<T extends Branch>
extends BinaryTree<T>
    CalculationTree is an implementation of the BinaryTree class that manages algebraic calculations, containing the 5 basic binary operations (+ - * / ^) plus the three trigonometric unary operations (sin cos tan).
    To respect the priority of operations, the begin method tries to split the expression with (+ -) first, then with (* /), and eventually with (^). Whenever a valid splitter is found, the branch ceases to be analyzed. Note that the class is abstract because the BinaryTree.generate(String) method needs to be defined, since the generic parameter is not defined. If you look for the most basic calculation tree handling simple branches, see ReducerTree for further information.
    Author:
    Antoine Tran
